{"lemma":"حِلْمُ","slug":"حِلْمُ","root":"ح.ل.م","root_slug":"ح-ل-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ل-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حِلْمُ","root":"حلم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8927","n8932","n8933","n8934","n8935","n8936","n8937"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D9%85%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dream (something) or about [with بِ (bi)] (something) while asleep","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dream (something) or about [with بِ (bi)] (something) while asleep; to muse, reflect, or meditate on [with بِ (bi)]; to vision, to image","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to experience the first seminal ejaculation; to mature physically or sexually; to attain puberty","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to experience the first seminal ejaculation; to become a legal adult or to be perceived as such","tags":["archaic","intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mature mentally or to be perceived as such; to act or think like an adult","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be gentle, forgiving, merciful, or lenient; to be mild-mannered","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to restrain oneself or to be restrained or checked (especially emotionally and psychologically); to forbear, to refrain, to abstain, to withhold; to be long-suffering, to be patient or enduring; to mellow","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلَمَ (ḥalama) (form I): dreaming","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a dream (something experienced during sleep); vision"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a wish, a desire, an aspiration; a daydream (something fantasised about or desired)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"utopia"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلَمَ (ḥalama) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sexual maturity; puberty","examples":[{"text":"وَإِذَا بَلَغَ ٱلْأَطْفَالُ مِنْكُمُ ٱلْحُلُمَ فَلْيَسْتَأْذِنُوا كَمَا ٱسْتَأْذَنَ ٱلَّذِينَ مِنْ قَبْلِهِمْ","english":"And if the children among you reach puberty, they shall ask for permission as those who did before them."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلُمَ (ḥaluma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mental, psychological, or comportmental maturity; prudence; rationality; discretion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"being long-suffering, self-restraint; forbearance, longanimity","examples":[{"text":"أَنْتَ أَكْثَرُ مِنِّي حِلْمًا.","english":"You are more patient than me."},{"text":"لَا يَغُرَّنَّكَ حِلْمِي فَصَبْرِي بَدَأَ يَنْفَدُ.","english":"Let not my forbearance deceive you, for my patience is running out."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tick(s), mite(s)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nipple(s), teat(s)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"callous-leaved gromwell (Moltkiopsis ciliata)","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Akin to Aramaic חֶלְמָא (ḥelmā), Classical Syriac ܚܠܡܐ (ḥelmā), Hebrew חֲלוֹם (ḥalóm), Amharic ሕልም (ḥəlm), Ugaritic 𐎈𐎍𐎎 (ḥlm). For the significations of the root in Arabic, compare م ن ي (m n y), whence أُمْنِيَة (ʔumniya, “a wish”) and مَنِيّ (maniyy, “a fluid considered conceptive; semen”)."},"ipa":["/ħulm/","/ħu.lum/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8927","headword_ar":"حَلَمَ","root":"Hlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haluma","text_ar":"حَلُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulomN","text_ar":"حُلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulumN","text_ar":"حُلُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the former is a contraction, (Msb,) [both used also as simple substs.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dreamed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saw a dream"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vision"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY nawomihi","text_ar":"فِى نَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his sleep;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtlm","text_ar":"احتلم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, ISd, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AnHlm","text_ar":"انحلم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISd, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHl~m","text_ar":"تحلّم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halama bihi","text_ar":"حَلَمَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, [in the CK, again, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haluma","text_ar":"حَلُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":632},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHl~m","text_ar":"تحلّم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halamahu","text_ar":"حَلَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dreamed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saw a dream"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vision, of it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he saw it in sleep."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halama","text_ar":"حَلَمَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAlmaroA^api","text_ar":"بِالمَرْاَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dreamed in his sleep that he was compressing the woman."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulomN","text_ar":"حُلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiHotilaAmN","text_ar":"اِحْتِلَامٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dreaming of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"copulation in sleep:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and the verbs are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halama","text_ar":"حَلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtlm","text_ar":"احتلم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And [hence,] both signify The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"experiencing an emission of the seminal fluid;"},{"kind":"text","text":"properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in dreaming;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and tropically if meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without dreaming, whether awake or in sleep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or by extension of the signification. (TA.) And hence, (Mgh,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halama","text_ar":"حَلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulomN","text_ar":"حُلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHtlm","text_ar":"احتلم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a boy)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attained to puberty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) [or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to virility."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haluma","text_ar":"حَلُمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm [to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"], inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilomN","text_ar":"حِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, forbearing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clement;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he forgave and concealed"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offences"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, moderate, gentle, deliberate, leisurely in his manner of proceeding"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of deportment &c., patient"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of hasty, grave, staid, sedate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he managed his soul and temper on the occasion of excitement of anger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilomN","text_ar":"حِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haloma Eanohu","text_ar":"حَلْمَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHl~m","text_ar":"تحلّم","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He treated him with forbearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clemency, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]: both signify the same. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaHolumu Eam~ano yasub~uhu","text_ar":"يَحْلُمُ عَمَّنْ يَسُبُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He treats with forbearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clemency,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him who reviles him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hml","text_ar":"حمل"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halima","text_ar":"حَلِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalamN","text_ar":"حَلَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"many ticks, such as are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halam","text_ar":"حَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  Also the same verb, (S, K,) with the same inf. n., (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a hide, or skin,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had in it worms, such as are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halam","text_ar":"حَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby it was spoilt and perforated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it became useless."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) A poet says, (S,) namely, El-Weleed Ibn-'Okbeh, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faA_in~aka waAlkitaAba A_ilaY EaliY~K\n                      \n                     \n                        ka*aAbigapK waqado Halima AlA^adiymu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For verily thou, as to the letter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing, to 'Alee, art like a woman tanning when the hide has become spoilt and perforated by worms"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, TA:) he was urging Mo'áwiyeh to contend in battle with 'Alee, [as though] saying to him, Thou labourest to rectify a matter that has become completely corrupt, like this woman who tans the hide that has become perforated and spoilt by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halam","text_ar":"حَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [The latter hemistich of this verse is a prov.: see Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 346.]       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halamahu","text_ar":"حَلَمَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalomN","text_ar":"حَلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He plucked the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halam","text_ar":"حَلَم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app., accord. to the K, the worms thus called from a hide, or skin;] as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hl~mhu","text_ar":"حلّمهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or, accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took from him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ticks called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halam","text_ar":"حَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","S","K","ISd","Mgh"]},{"entry_id":"n8932","headword_ar":"حَلْمٌ","root":"Hlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilomN","text_ar":"حِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n8933","headword_ar":"حُلْمٌ","root":"Hlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halama","text_ar":"حَلَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulumN","text_ar":"حُلُمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dream,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vision in sleep;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulumN","text_ar":"حُلُمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) accord. to most of the lexicologists, as well as F,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^oyaA","text_ar":"رُوْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": or it is specially"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is evil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rw^yA","text_ar":"رويا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the contr.: this is corroborated by the trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~uw^oyaA mina A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"الرُّوْيَا مِنَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlHulomu mina Al$~ayoTaAni","text_ar":"وَالحُلْمُ مِنَ الشَّيْطَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rw^yA","text_ar":"رويا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is from God, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hlm","text_ar":"حلم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is from the Devil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (MF:) and by the phrase, in the Kur [xii. 44 and xxi. 5],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDogaAvu","text_ar":"اَضْغَاثُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHolaAmK","text_ar":"اَحْلَامٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The confused circumstances of dreams,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of evil dreams"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but each is used in the place of the other: (TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHolaAmN","text_ar":"اَحْلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the pl. (K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHolaAmu naAy^imK","text_ar":"اَحْلَامُ نَايِمٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The dreams of a sleeper;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of thick cloths,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKh, Z, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"striped, of the people of El-Medeeneh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","MF","TA","IKh","Z"]},{"entry_id":"n8934","headword_ar":"حِلْمٌ","root":"Hlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Forbearance; clemency;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality of forgiving and concealing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offences"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moderation; gentleness; deliberateness; a leisurely manner of proceding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of deportment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"patience,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning contr."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of hastiness: gravity; staidness; sedateness; calmness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaApN","text_ar":"اَنَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"these qualities with power"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to exercise the contrary qualities"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaApN","text_ar":"اَنَاةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukuwnN","text_ar":"سُكُونٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qudorapN","text_ar":"قُدْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quw~apN","text_ar":"قُوَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kull p. 167:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"management of one's soul and temper on the occasion of excitement of anger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tranquillity on the occasion of emotion of anger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"delay in requiting the wrongdoer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KT:) it is described by the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viqalN","text_ar":"ثِقَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gravity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as its contr. ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"safahN","text_ar":"سَفَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is described by the terms"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiq~apN","text_ar":"خِقَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EajalN","text_ar":"عَجَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or levity, or lightness, and hastiness: (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rjH","text_ar":"رجح"},{"kind":"text","text":":) also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) which is not its proper signification, but a meaning assigned because it is one of the results of intelligence: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalomN","text_ar":"حَلْمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, is likewise said to have this last meaning; but this requires consideration: (TA:) the former is one of those inf. ns. that are [used as simple substs., and therefore] pluralized: (ISd, TA:) the pl. [of pauc.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHolaAmN","text_ar":"اَحْلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuluwmN","text_ar":"حُلُومٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) Hence, in the Kur [lii. 32],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amo taA^omuruhumo A^aHolaAmuhumo","text_ar":"اَمْ تَاْمُرُهُمْ اَحْلَامُهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bih`*aA","text_ar":"بِهٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) said to mean (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Do their understandings enjoin them this?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwluw AlA^aHolaAmi","text_ar":"اُولُو الاَحْلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persons of understanding."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","K","TA","KT","ISd"]},{"entry_id":"n8935","headword_ar":"حَلَمٌ","root":"Hlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalamapN","text_ar":"حَلَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n8936","headword_ar":"حَلِمٌ","root":"Hlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"many ticks, such as are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halam","text_ar":"حَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spoilt by the abundance of those ticks that were upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also A hide, or skin,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spoilt and perforated by"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the worms termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halam","text_ar":"حَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":": and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliymN","text_ar":"حَلِيمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in like manner,] a hide, or skin,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spoilt by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halam","text_ar":"حَلَم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"before it is stripped off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaAqN HalimapN","text_ar":"عَنَاقٌ حَلِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A she-kid"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose skin has been spoilt by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halam","text_ar":"حَلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, * TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHolimapN","text_ar":"تَحْلِمَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHaAlimu","text_ar":"تَحَالِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalimapN","text_ar":"حَلِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HilaAmN","text_ar":"حِلَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n8937","headword_ar":"حُلُمٌ","root":"Hlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HulomN","text_ar":"حُلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dream of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"copulation in sleep."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaga AlHuluma","text_ar":"بَلَغَ الحُلُمَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He attained to puberty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"virility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in an absolute sense. (TA.) It is said in the Kur [xxiv. 58],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA_i*aA balaga AlA^aTofaAlu minokumu AlHuluma faloyasotaA^o*inuwA","text_ar":"وَاـِذَا بَلَغَ الاَطْفَالُ مِنْكُمُ الحُلُمَ فَلْيَسْتَاْذِنُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And when your children attain to puberty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"virility, they shall ask permission"},{"kind":"text","text":"to come into your presence]. (TA.) [And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoraAsu","text_ar":"اَضْرَاسُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHulumi","text_ar":"الحُلُمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aDoraAsu AlEaqoli","text_ar":"اَضْرَاسُ العَقْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Drs","text_ar":"ضرس"},{"kind":"text","text":",) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The teeth of puberty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wisdom-teeth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] so called because they grow after the attaining to puberty, and the completion of the intellectual faculties: (S, L, Msb, all in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nj*","text_ar":"نجذ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) they are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four teeth that come forth after the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"teeth have become strong."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Drs","text_ar":"ضرس"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}